red form of English   Salisbury  ."]},{"name":"Salsbery","meanings":["English: variant of   Salisbury  ."]},{"name":"Salsbury","meanings":["English (Worcestershire): variant of   Salisbury  .","Jewish (American): adoption of the English surname (see 1 above) in place of   Salomon   or some other Jewish name beginning with <i>Sa-</i>."]},{"name":"Salsberry","meanings":["English: variant of   Salisbury  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Salisbury was born in 1443. He had at least 1 daughter with Janet Griffith."},"et":{"1443–":"1443–Surnud","1470–1516":"1470–1516","1470–1551":"1470–1551","1443–Male":"1443–Surnud","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1443":"1443","1551":"1551","1470":"1470","1516":"1516","Lleweni, Henllan, Denbighshire, Wales":"Henllan, Denbighshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1443–":"1443–Kuollut","1470–1516":"1470–1516","1470–1551":"1470–1551","1443–Male":"1443–Kuollut","about 1470":"noin 1470","1443":"1443","1551":"1551","1470":"1470","1516":"1516","Lleweni, Henllan, Denbighshire, Wales":"Henllan, Denbighshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1443–":"1443–Décédé","1470–1516":"1470–1516","1470–1551":"1470–1551","1443–Male":"1443–Décédé","about 1470":"environ 1470","1443":"1443","1551":"1551","1470":"1470","1516":"1516","Lleweni, Henllan, Denbighshire, Wales":"Henllan, Denbighshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Thomas Salisbury est né en 1443. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Janet Griffith."},"de":{"1443–":"1443–Verstorben","1470–1516":"1470–1516","1470–1551":"1470–1551","1443–M